content:
Well, this one surely made me reflect about how boring my life is. Since I became an adult, I forgot how wonderful is to have something to believe and admire, eventhough it doesn't exist. Is it really worthy growing up? Maybe we could all be happier if our imagination didn't fade away when we less expected it...
{STORY - 9/10}
This anime is focuses on explaining this "chuunibyou", or "eight grade syndrom", a psichological disorder that affects highly-influenciable pre-teenagers. Those described to play lots of videogames and watch too much anime are said to be weak-willed and then, being unable to distinguish reality from their own worlds,they can't socialize very well.


Yuuta suffered from it and starting High School on a place far away from his previous classmates would be the perfect opportunity to start over, make friends and enjoy a normal life. This was his plan, until an unexpected encounter with Rikka, a girl that still suffered from chuunibyou, changed everything.


With the sole objective of finding the "Ethereal Horizon", Rikka founded a club, along with Yuuta, to research magic. A few more members would be accepted, but its main purpose was only aimed by both Rikka and Sanae. On the meanwhile, Yuuta tries to understand why Rikka still has chuunibyou and a beautiful love story takes focus after some time.


{ART - 9/10}


Overall art impressed me. However, all the imaginary battles draw a lot of my attention. Eventhough they aren't real, we can see amazing effects and magic casting, side by side with intense movements and attacks on exciting combat sequences. Both OP and ED themes are really nice and original. The use of a subtle design for both characters and scenarios was the right choice, perfect combination!


{SOUND - 10/10}


It's possible noticing a very strong dedication on making a suitable backgrounding for most scenes. All songs are well chosen for all situations and effects used on battles earlier mentionated just makes them mlre thrilling. Songs featured on both OP and ED themes are incredibly matching!


{CHARACTERS - 7/10}


Both Yuuta and Shinka are students trying to forget their embarassing past, when they suffered from chuunibyou. They want normal lives, and Yuuta tries to make Rikka accept reality, even if this means destroying her dreams.


Rikka is the trigger to all this confusion. She hides her emotions behind this "Evil Eye" disguise and getting closer to Yuuta quickly awakens her deepedt feelings. She admires Yuuta and he's also one of her reasons to act the ways she does.


Rikka's "servant", Sanae, also suffers from chuunibyou and joins her on this quest for the Ethereal Horizon. She seems to have the most concern on Rikka's life and struggles to keep everything the way it is.


{ENJOYMENT - 10/10}


Learning something new from an anime is always good, but getting emotive and amazed is even better! Combining comedy with drama and romance is quite simple. However, a perfect match is tough and they did it. I can't say how much I loved this one!


{OVERALL - 9/10}


Everyone as a child wants to quickly grow up and make everything adults do, be free, have the "real fun". This is way wrong. You can't give up on your inocence just to look more mature. That's what makes youth so vivid, happy, full of hope... Dreams are important and some imagination isn't bad at all... This anime teaches us to not let who we are behind, to keep believing, to see beauty on our actions and on this world. Because seeing what others don't understand makes us unique... It may be childish, but is a whole better than living a dull life...
